%N A394334 Decimal expansion of the asymptotic mean of the number of exponential unitary divisors of the greatest common divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random.
%F A394334 Equals lim_{m->oo} (1/m^2) * Sum_{i,j=1..m} A278908(gcd(i, j)).
%F A394334 Equals Product_{p prime} (1-1/p^2)*(1 + Sum_{k >= 1} ud(k)/p^(2*k)), where ud(k) is the number of unitary divisors of k (A034444).
%e A394334 1.078304786696831022734548475012806056531948835472367...
%o A394334 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1-1/p^2) *(1 + sum(k = 1, m, 2^omega(k)/p^(2*k))));
%o A394334 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A394334 Cf. A034444, A278908, A394333.
%K A394334 nonn,cons
%O A394334 1,3
%A A394334 _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 17 2026
